# =============================================================================
# npm configuration for the TallyJ frontend
# =============================================================================

# esbuild lifecycle script approval
#
# esbuild (pulled in by Vite) runs a postinstall script to fetch the correct
# native binary for the current OS/architecture. This is safe and expected.
#
# Current state with npm:
# - There is no stable public .npmrc key (e.g. allow-scripts.* or approve-scripts.*)
#   that works without triggering "Unknown project config" warnings.
#
# The officially supported way is to run this command once from this directory
# after a fresh `git clone` or when the warning appears:
#
#     npm approve-scripts esbuild
#
# After running the command above, the warning should no longer appear on
# subsequent `npm install` runs in this environment.
